 Install Cypress
Create a new directory for your project or navigate to your existing project directory. Then install Cypress using npm:

mkdir cypress-test && cd cypress-test
npm init -y
npm install cypress --save-dev


Install Required Dependencies for Cypress

sudo apt install libnss3 libnspr4 libxss1 libasound2 libatk1.0-0 libatk-bridge2.0-0 libcups2 libdrm2 libdbus-1-3 libxkbcommon0 libgbm1 libgtk-3-0 -y



Open Cypress
You can open Cypress for the first time to ensure everything is set up correctly:


npx cypress open



This will open the Cypress Test Runner. Close it after the initial setup.



